menu "bb_cache"

config BB_CACHE_MAX_TOPICS
    int "Maximum number of registered cache topics"
    default 32
    range 1 64
    help
        Fixed-size registry capacity. Each entry holds a fixed-size key
        buffer, optional owned struct buffer, serializer fn, and a mutex.
        Increase if more than 8 state topics need caching.

config BB_CACHE_KEY_MAX
    int "Maximum length of a registered cache key (bytes, incl. NUL)"
    default 96
    range 8 256
    help
        Fixed-size per-entry key buffer. bb_cache_register() copies the
        caller's key into this buffer (the caller no longer needs to keep
        the string alive) and rejects keys of length >= this value with
        BB_ERR_INVALID_ARG. The default (96) historically matched the
        deleted bb_sub component's ingress topic cap, sized for
        dynamically-routed MQTT topics; static breadboard keys (e.g.
        "update.available") are far shorter. Standing cost is
        BB_CACHE_KEY_MAX * BB_CACHE_MAX_TOPICS bytes.

config BB_CACHE_SWEEP_ENABLE
    bool "Enable periodic age-out eviction sweep backstop"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, a periodic background sweep (bb_cache_foreach) evicts
        BB_CACHE_EVICT_AGE_OUT keys past their evict_age_ms even if nothing
        reads them -- LAZY (read-time) eviction only fires on an actual
        read. The sweep starts via a pre_http registry hook (bbtool:init
        marker in bb_cache.h); no application code changes are needed.
        Disabled by default: LAZY
        eviction alone is sufficient for read-driven keys; enable this for
        keys that may go unread for long stretches (e.g. a disconnected
        ingress source) and still need their memory reclaimed.

config BB_CACHE_SWEEP_PERIOD_MS
    int "Age-out sweep period (ms)"
    default 30000
    range 1000 3600000
    depends on BB_CACHE_SWEEP_ENABLE
    help
        Interval between sweep passes. Should be well under the shortest
        registered evict_age_ms among AGE_OUT keys, or eviction lags behind
        the configured window.

config BB_CACHE_SWEEP_WORKER_STACK
    int "bb_cache eviction sweep worker task stack (bytes)"
    default 8192
    range 4096 16384
    depends on BB_CACHE_SWEEP_ENABLE
    help
        FreeRTOS task stack for the sweep's dedicated bb_timer_worker task.
        Each sweep pass's call chain is sweep_cb -> evict_if_aged_out_locked
        -> bb_cache_delete_if_generation -> the evict-notify hook -> (when
        a composer has installed one, e.g. bb_mdns_cache) an ARBITRARY
        consumer-supplied on_remove callback -- the depth of that last hop
        is not something bb_cache controls or can bound. 8192 matches
        the house precedent for a TLS-tier background worker stack (a
        callback chain of unknown depth) rather than the ESP-IDF
        pthread default (~3072 bytes) the sweep used before this
        firmware-review fix, which was unsafe once the sweep became live.

config BB_CACHE_SWEEP_WORKER_PRIORITY
    int "bb_cache eviction sweep worker task priority"
    default 1
    range 1 24
    depends on BB_CACHE_SWEEP_ENABLE
    help
        FreeRTOS task priority for the sweep worker. Default 1 (lowest
        application priority) matches the house background-worker default --
        background housekeeping should not compete with time-sensitive
        application tasks.

config BB_CACHE_SWEEP_WORKER_CORE
    int "bb_cache eviction sweep worker task core affinity"
    default -1
    range -1 1
    depends on BB_CACHE_SWEEP_ENABLE
    help
        -1 = no affinity (default, runs on either core); 0 or 1 = pin the
        sweep worker task to that core.

endmenu
